{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἄλφῐτον</b>, τό, <br /> <b>barley-groats,</b> <i>singular</i> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] only in phrase ἀλφίτου ἀκτή[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 11.631, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.355, 14.429, and in Medicine texts, 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 6.507: elsewhere in _plural_ ἄλφιτα, opposed to ἀλείατα, which see, ἄ. μυελὸν ἀνδρῶν 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.290, +others, 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.119\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>], frequently in <i>Attic dialect</i>; used to sprinkle over roast meat, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 18.560, compare 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.77\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; especially over sacrificial victims, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 14.429: ἐπ᾽ ἀλφίτου πίνειν\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] to drink wine with <b>barley-groats</b> in it, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Epinicus Comicus 1\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]:—of this was made a kind of <b>barley-water,</b> πιεῖν ἄλφιτα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “ἐπιδημίαι” 5.10\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also, <b>poultices,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Dioscorides (Dioscurides) Medicus 4.87\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]: also used as <b>hair-powder</b> by κανηφόροι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hermippus Comicus 26. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> generally, <b>meal, groats,</b> ἄ. πύρινα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “Acut.(Sp.)” 53\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἄ. φακῶν καὶ ὀρόβων[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Int.” 23; even λίθοιο ἄλφιτα 5th-6th c.AD: Orphica “Lithica” 212. \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>one's daily bread,</b> 'bread and cheese', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 219, “Nu.” 106, etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G6245","accentedUnicode":"ἄλφιτον","shortDef":"toasted grain","mediumDef":"toasted grain","stepGloss":"toasted grain","stepTransliteration":"alfiton","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}